Package com.tangosol.util.function

Interface Remote.ToIntBiFunction<T,​U>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the first argument to the function
    U - the type of the second argument to the function
    All Superinterfaces:
    Serializable, ToIntBiFunction<T,​U>
    Enclosing class:
    Remote
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.
    @FunctionalInterface
public static interface Remote.ToIntBiFunction<T,​U>
extends ToIntBiFunction<T,​U>, Serializable
    Represents a function that accepts two arguments and produces an int-valued result. This is the int-producing primitive specialization for Remote.BiFunction.

    This is a functional interface whose functional method is ToIntBiFunction.applyAsInt(Object, Object).

    See Also:
